Volunteers of the Federal Government Social Investment Programme Npower are smiling to the bank as Npower pays January Stipend. The payment commenced this morning as alerts from First City Monument Bank has been spotted. Volunteers of the scheme had been affected by the epileptic system of payment which characterized the scheme last year. With this development, volunteers can now work hard and contribute their quota to the service they are assigned. The 2016 batch of volunteers have also been paid as they await their exit packages.